You know, everybody in Willisville and the surrounding area believed that if they bother my family,

00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:04.000
it was a whole lot of killing when I take place.

00:27:04.000 --> 00:27:13.000
They believed that because my brother had been in a real bad racial situation, Troy.

00:27:13.000 --> 00:27:22.000
I got his memory of that. He was the only black member that went to a little town called McNeil, Arkansas.

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:26.000
And he got a job working on the railroad road.

00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:37.000
He didn't, he wasn't on a train. He was going to hard work putting old spikes on all that to keep it up.

00:27:37.000 --> 00:27:49.000
And when he went, wherever they went, and on the way back when they got to McNeil, Arkansas, they told Troy he had to get off the train

00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:55.000
because he couldn't, blacks couldn't, well, Negro, one of the black folks, and there's Negro in the middle of the day.

00:27:55.000 --> 00:27:59.000
Negroes couldn't ride the train through McNeil, Arkansas's little small town.

00:27:59.000 --> 00:28:04.000
And my brother, Troy, wouldn't get off the train.

00:28:04.000 --> 00:28:08.000
And just like my parents, he had his weapon.

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:13.000
And well, it was a hard knockdown fight.

00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:21.000
You know, he stabbed and cut a whole bunch of white folks, and then they chased him and shot him up pretty bad.

00:28:21.000 --> 00:28:30.000
But he got through the wash and all that, and so the white people decided that they were going to come to our house and kill him.

00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:38.000
And Mr. Chester Waters is the guy who in Williamsburg had the little store, the both little stores there.

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:44.000
He told the people to don't, don't y'all go over there. Y'all are going to get killed.

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:54.000
And so my dad had some brothers, some cousin, and you had to go down through these walls, this dirt road to get over to the farm.

00:28:54.000 --> 00:29:00.000
And about dark at night, he was coming in out of the get-troward.

00:29:00.000 --> 00:29:08.000
Man, there was so much shooting and so many people got hit, and I heard him scream, oh, I've been hit.

00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:18.000
And what dad had did, and his brothers, when they were shooting people, they went to them and took their guns.

00:29:18.000 --> 00:29:21.000
They let them go, but they took all their guns.

00:29:21.000 --> 00:29:28.000
And so it was kind of known that the McKinney's wanted to focus on mess wet.

00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:32.000
And it was a lot of them. It was a bunch of.

00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:34.000
About 68.

00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:37.000
No, no, excuse me, how old were you then?

00:29:37.000 --> 00:29:42.000
Oh, eight, nine, about a pack.

00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:43.000
So really 50s.

00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:56.000
Yeah, I went up to Williamsville, Arkansas, Arkansas and go, dad had made the comment, said if they come down here and mess with me, I'm going to kick that ass.

00:29:56.000 --> 00:29:58.000
