00:32:08.000 --> 00:32:14.000
this is one of my boys. Ernest Jones boys. Them boys are sweet kind.

00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:18.000
I mean, he really just painted his beautiful picture. They are smart.

00:32:18.000 --> 00:32:23.000
And I want all the professors to keep their eyes on him. He's a good student.

00:32:23.000 --> 00:32:29.000
Don't be putting him over in social status. He's a good man, algebra.

00:32:29.000 --> 00:32:37.000
He came from a high school that had all of that. Because when the guy asked me, he said,

00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:44.000
when God told me that you might need to take preliminary courses, he said, you from a small town.

00:32:44.000 --> 00:32:52.000
I said, yeah. He said, what did you have in high school? I said, I had algebra.

00:32:52.000 --> 00:32:59.000
I had trick and geometry. I had physics. I had biology, chemistry.

00:32:59.000 --> 00:33:06.000
He said, man, what got a school that you go to as I had a school that was very good school.

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:17.000
And matter of fact, the principal imported. He handpicked teachers from all around to come and at that school.

00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:19.000
Was it a good fight?

00:33:19.000 --> 00:33:29.000
No, it was a school, but it was there were four schools in Arkansas.

00:33:29.000 --> 00:33:38.000
And there was built way back in the 1931 by the Ohio.

00:33:38.000 --> 00:33:50.000
I think they were, they were the, it's a group out of New York somewhere built the school way back.

00:33:50.000 --> 00:33:56.000
Because I know our 1929. And the school was built.

00:33:56.000 --> 00:34:03.000
And they had vision of folks coming because the school was built with Dometaurus.

00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:07.000
So these teachers came from other place and they lived right down campus.

00:34:07.000 --> 00:34:14.000
I think the Quakers are Quakers of. And there was two all black school districts.

00:34:14.000 --> 00:34:19.000
Mine was one of them. And the other one was Arkansas City where I opened the magazine.

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:28.000
Johnson Man came out of it. So we had, unlike a lot of other school, we had books because we could float bonds.

00:34:28.000 --> 00:34:35.000
And we had the books not because a lot of the white school give out all books to the black schools.

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:40.000
But no, we had good books and we had good teachers and things like that. So I had a good start.

00:34:40.000 --> 00:34:47.000
