00:36:02.000 --> 00:36:05.000
And they were going to get put out of school and all that.

00:36:05.000 --> 00:36:09.000
And he said, I want you to, I like to meet those guys.

00:36:09.000 --> 00:36:13.000
And that's when Worth Long, it's not a very Worth Long.

00:36:13.000 --> 00:36:21.000
And when Worth Long came down and Worth Long and Bill Hansen.

00:36:21.000 --> 00:36:25.000
And I hadn't met Worth a little bit late on my hand.

00:36:25.000 --> 00:36:33.000
And so a few days later they rolled cream and started talking.

00:36:33.000 --> 00:36:42.000
And so Bill Hansen said, dang man, you've already done what we tried to do.

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:48.000
Now it's your hometown.

00:36:48.000 --> 00:36:54.000
And then when I said, well, that's how I was raised.

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:57.000
He said, man, this would be a piece of cake for you.

00:36:57.000 --> 00:37:01.000
But then they, that wasn't when they were trying to get it started.

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:04.000
But they said that they were working in the Lurak and do some things.

00:37:04.000 --> 00:37:11.000
But when we come back to Pinebluff, we need to sit down and talk because this is a college town.

00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:14.000
And there's a lot of segregation here.

00:37:14.000 --> 00:37:17.000
And I hear you guys are down here.

00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:20.000
They all got all these McDonald's and all of this.

00:37:20.000 --> 00:37:22.000
And the black people can't go to.

00:37:22.000 --> 00:37:28.000
And this city is driven by the university here.

00:37:28.000 --> 00:37:35.000
So that's, and that's how I met them.

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:41.000
